    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/07-inference-serving/08-disaggregated-chunked-prefill.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Prefill is compute-bound and decode is memory-bandwidth-bound because of WEIGHT REUSE: a long prompt pushes T_p tokens through each weight matrix loaded once from HBM (fat matrix x matrix, high arithmetic intensity), while decode streams the entire weight set from HBM to advance just ONE token per sequence (skinny vector x matrix, low arithmetic intensity) \u2014 same bytes moved, vastly fewer FLOPs per byte.; These opposite resource profiles mean the phases want different hardware (fast-FLOP GPUs for prefill, high-HBM-bandwidth GPUs for decode) and actively FIGHT each other when mixed on one GPU under continuous batching.; Prefill-decode interference: one long prefill monopolizes the GPU for tens of ms, so every in-flight decode sequence is stalled and the next token arrives late \u2014 a bursty P99 inter-token-latency (ITL) spike even though average latency looks fine.; Chunked prefill bounds that stall: slice the long prompt into fixed-size chunks (C ~ 512) and interleave one chunk with a full decode step every iteration, so decode is never fully preempted and ITL inflation is capped at one chunk's compute time \u2014 at a small TTFT cost.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  prefill-decode-reuse-contrast, disagg-pd-architecture\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
