    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/10-multimodal-and-arch/03-audio-speech-multimodal.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Audio becomes machine-learnable in two ways: a continuous Mel spectrogram (STFT + Mel filterbank, ~200x shorter than the waveform) for encoder models like Whisper, or discrete codec tokens for generative LMs.; Residual Vector Quantization is a coarse-to-fine approximation: each successive codebook quantizes only the RESIDUAL left by the previous one, so the sum of K nearest entries reconstructs the encoder vector and level-1 alone already captures coarse structure.; The token-budget tension: faithful codec audio costs ~600 tokens/s (~200x the transcript), forcing hierarchy, coarse-only modeling, or continuous inputs.; Semantic vs acoustic disentanglement: level-1 (or semantic) tokens encode WHAT is said, higher levels encode HOW it sounds, which lets level-1 stand in for text in a speech LM.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  rvq-residual-cascade, audio-llm-transfer-curriculum\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
